### C++-Specific Best Practices Table
| Practice | Rationale | Example |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| Smart Pointers | Prevents memory leaks | std::unique_ptr<int> p(new int(42)); |
| Const Correctness | Compile-time safety | void Func(const std::string& str); |
| RAII | Resource management | class File { File() { /* open */ } ~File() { /* close */ } }; |
| No Raw Loops | Use algorithms | std::for_each(v.begin(), v.end(), func); |
| Exception Safety | Handle failures | try { /* code */ } catch (const std::exception& e) { /* handle */ } |

